      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "QUINLEE BALE (2) missed the frame latest (30.25) when eighth over 515m at Sandown in a Grade 5. Has already won two times from this draw. Looks well placed and should feature. LIVING (7) is a capable type and proved too classy last time to win by 0.8 lengths at Bendigo in a handy 23.91 beating This Black Duck. Makes plenty of appeal on the back of that last-start win. PIEBALD (1) has been beaten for early speed lately, last time finishing fourth (22.47) in a Free For All at Shepparton. Solid record at the distance winning four races. Yet to miss the placings from three starts out of this box. Can figure in the finish. PAW BASTOW (3) cannot be left out after placing last start.",
